    <localTopics>
        <fullName>Post_Visit_Actions_16jak000001pYiD</fullName>
        <canEscalate>false</canEscalate>
        <description>WHEN TO USE: Call this action when you complete a visit/meeting with a healthcare provider, clinic, hospital, or doctor. This orchestrator intelligently handles THREE OPERATIONS in sequence: (1) CREATE VISIT LOG - Documents what was discussed, attendees, outcomes, and any referral opportunities. (2) CREATE FOLLOW-UP TASK (optional) - If user mentions action items like &quot;send brochure&quot;, &quot;call them back&quot;, &quot;schedule follow-up&quot; - create a task assigned to sales team with 3-day default deadline. (3) SEND EMAIL (optional) - If user asks to notify the doctor/provider, sends professional healthcare industry email with brochure attachment. BUSINESS VALUE: Automatically creates complete post-visit documentation, ensures no follow-up actions are forgotten, and establishes communication trail. USE EXAMPLES: &quot;Log my visit to Apollo Hospitals - discussed oncology program with Dr. Mehta, and send them our brochure&quot; → Creates visit log + task + email. &quot;Document my Manipal meeting about cardiology partnership&quot; → Creates visit log only (no task/email needed). REQUIRED INPUTS: Clinic/hospital name + what was discussed. OPTIONAL INPUTS: Doctor name, referral notes, expense amount, follow-up actions. OUTPUTS: Visit log ID (tracked in CRM), task ID (if created), email confirmation, and success message.</description>
        <developerName>Post_Visit_Actions_16jak000001pYiD</developerName>
        <genAiPluginInstructions>
            <description>You are an AI Agent.</description>
            <developerName>instruction0_179ak000002yW3u</developerName>
            <language>en_US</language>
            <masterLabel>instruction0_179ak000002yW3u</masterLabel>
            <sortOrder>1</sortOrder>
        </genAiPluginInstructions>
        <language>en_US</language>
        <localActionLinks>
            <functionName>Post_Visit_Documentation_TaskCreation_179ak000002yW3u</functionName>
        </localActionLinks>
        <localActions>
            <fullName>Post_Visit_Documentation_TaskCreation_179ak000002yW3u</fullName>
            <description>FULL POST-VISIT WORKFLOW: Call this when documenting a clinic/hospital visit with visit log creation as the PRIMARY operation. THIS ACTION handles: (1) CREATE VISIT LOG (REQUIRED) - Documents what was discussed, attendees, outcomes, referral opportunities. (2) CREATE FOLLOW-UP TASK (optional) - If user mentions action items (&quot;call them&quot;, &quot;follow up&quot;). WHEN TO USE: &quot;Log my visit to Apollo Hospitals with Dr. Mehta - discussed oncology program and future partnership opportunities. Also create a follow-up task to call them on Tuesday.&quot; REQUIRED INPUTS: Clinic/hospital name + visit summary (what was discussed). OPTIONAL INPUTS: Doctor name, referral notes, expense tracking, follow-up actions. OUTPUTS: Visit log ID (CRM record), task ID (if created), success message.</description>
            <developerName>Post_Visit_Documentation_TaskCreation_179ak000002yW3u</developerName>
            <invocationTarget>PostVisitLogOrchestrator</invocationTarget>
            <invocationTargetType>apex</invocationTargetType>
            <isConfirmationRequired>false</isConfirmationRequired>
            <isIncludeInProgressIndicator>true</isIncludeInProgressIndicator>
            <localDeveloperName>Post_Visit_Documentation_TaskCreation</localDeveloperName>
            <masterLabel>Post Visit Documentation, Task Creation</masterLabel>
            <progressIndicatorMessage>Procesing</progressIndicatorMessage>
            <source>Post_Visit_Documentation_TaskCreation</source>
        </localActions>
